. Base faced scalability hiccups during peak memecoin frenzies and competition from Solana's speed or Arbitrum's DeFi depth. Market downturns in early 2025 dipped TVL temporarily, and regulatory scrutiny on L2s looms. Yet, Base's Coinbase backing—providing compliance moats and fiat bridges—has buffered these, with 85% of 2025's L2 activity funneled through it. 

